SIMPLE: flapdragon
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flapdragon
<hw>Flap"drag`on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
game in which the players catch raisins out burning brandy, and swallow
them blazing.</def> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The thing thus caught and eaten.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cakes and ale, and <qex>flapdragons</qex> and mummer's plays, and
all the happy sports of Christians night.</q> <rj><qau>C.
Kingsley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flapdragon</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Flapdragon
<hw>Flap"drag`on</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To swallow whole, as a
flapdragon; to devour.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>See how the sea <qex>flapdragoned</qex> it.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flap-eared</ent>⟦br⟧
